  1050â†’## Tips
  1052â†’### Sending form data
  1054â†’Sending form data in Ky is identical to `fetch`. Just pass a [`FormData`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FormData) instance to the `body` option. The `Content-Type` header will be automatically set to `multipart/form-data`, overriding any existing `Content-Type` header.
  1055â†’
  1056â†’```js
  1057â†’import ky from 'ky';
  1058â†’
  1059â†’// `multipart/form-data`
  1060â†’const formData = new FormData();
  1061â†’formData.append('food', 'fries');
  1062â†’formData.append('drink', 'icetea');
  1063â†’
  1064â†’const response = await ky.post(url, {body: formData});
  1065â†’```
  1066â†’
  1067â†’If you want to send the data in `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` format, you will need to encode the data with [`URLSearchParams`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/URLSearchParams). Like `FormData`, this will override any existing `Content-Type` headers.
  1068â†’
  1069â†’```js
  1070â†’import ky from 'ky';
  1071â†’
  1072â†’// `application/x-www-form-urlencoded`
  1073â†’const searchParams = new URLSearchParams();
  1074â†’searchParams.set('food', 'fries');
  1075â†’searchParams.set('drink', 'icetea');
  1076â†’
  1077â†’const response = await ky.post(url, {body: searchParams});
  1078â†’```
  1079â†’
